# Rails 8 Specific Rules

- Use `rails new appname --api --database=postgresql` for API-only apps
- Solid Queue is the default background job adapter in Rails 8 — do NOT add Sidekiq unless asked
- Solid Cache is the default cache store — do NOT add Redis unless asked
- Propshaft is the default asset pipeline — irrelevant for API-only but do not add Sprockets
- Use `config.api_only = true` in application.rb — already set by --api flag
- Do NOT include ActionView, ActionMailer middleware unless explicitly needed
- Authentication: Rails 8 has built-in `has_secure_password` — use Devise + JWT for this project as specified
- Do NOT use `protect_from_forgery` in API-only mode
- Use `before_action :authenticate_user!` pattern for JWT auth